[I think the journalist is confused -- there have been 8 deaths, but not
all of them in patients in Brasilia. All the cases have been contracted
outside the Capital District in rural areas. But a risk of urbanization
does exist; the vector mosquito, _Aedes aegypti_ has been found in Brasilia
& its satellite cities. Measures are being
taken to implement source reduction.
When you vaccinate 32 million people, somebody is sure to die shortly
afterwards by simple random chance. I have not seen any evidence that the
unfortunate person died of yellow fever. - Mod.JW
....................................jw/es
